  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. NOTE (W-AR-05 / D3): One validation result (vr-cyclic-fatigue) references experimental data obtained under cyclic fatigue loading at 5 Hz rather than the quasi-static monotonic compression-bending regime declared in the COU. The comparator is well-documented and plausible on first read, but the loading regime is fundamentally mismatched to the COU; additionally, that result object omits the comparedAgainst link entirely, removing the machine-readable traceability required to detect the mismatch automatically.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/f1717-static-cb-noncannulated",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/fea-reproduces-f1717-cb-within-10pct",
