    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-cyclic-fatigue",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Cyclic fatigue stiffness degradation comparison (N=8) — supplementary validation",
      "description": "As supplementary evidence of model fidelity, the FEA ensemble was exercised against N=8 cyclic fatigue tests performed at 5 Hz sinusoidal loading (R-ratio 0.1, peak load 600 N) per ASTM F1717 fatigue annex. Secant stiffness at 10 000 cycles was extracted from both simulation and experiment. The FEA predicted stiffness within 7.3% of the mean experimental value, which the assessment team cited as additional confidence in the constitutive model. However, this loading regime — dynamic, cyclic, 5 Hz — is categorically different from the quasi-static monotonic compression-bending regime declared in the COU. The comparator population (fatigue specimens pre-conditioned to 10 000 cycles) is not representative of the monotonic failure mode the COU model is intended to predict. Despite the apparent numerical agreement, the inference drawn from this result is methodologically unsound: agreement under cyclic fatigue loading does not validate quasi-static yield prediction. This result is therefore an undercutting defeater (D3) for the validation argument."
    }
